description: Remote request schema, e.g. how TSP should call MaaS-backend

cost.description: A fare/price as billed by a TSP from MaaS in EUR

anyOf.description: Accepted monetary unit in ISO 4127 format, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217#cite_note-1

leg.description: A leg delta, containing any subset of the valid properties

anyOf.description: A mode that only involves waiting in the current location
A mode that involves changing transports
A mode that involves using your personal vehicle or legs
A mode that involves transit with fixed schedules
A mode that is available on-demand for your personal use

waitingMode.description: A mode that only involves waiting in the current location

transferMode.description: A mode that involves changing transports

personalMode.description: A mode that involves using your personal vehicle or legs

publicTransitMode.description: A mode that involves transit with fixed schedules

privateTransitMode.description: A mode that is available on-demand for your personal use

departureDelay.description: duration in milliseconds (negative values permitted), https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unix_time

from.description: A place, as a location-name pair with name and address

allOf.description: No-numeric precision version of MaaS core location

lat.description: No-numeric precision version of MaaS core latitude

lon.description: No-numeric precision version of MaaS core longitude

to.description: A place, as a location-name pair with name and address

allOf.description: No-numeric precision version of MaaS core location

lat.description: No-numeric precision version of MaaS core latitude

lon.description: No-numeric precision version of MaaS core longitude

meta.description: TSP/mode-specific additional information. The TSP adapter should set MODE_{mode} with defined data, otherwise 'meta' can be used freely.

location.description: Geographic latitude-longitude object in WGS-84 system, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System

lat.description: Geographic latitude (north-south axis) in WGS-84 system, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System

lon.description: Geographic longitude (east-west axis) in WGS-84 system, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System

location.description: Geographic latitude-longitude object in WGS-84 system, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System

lat.description: Geographic latitude (north-south axis) in WGS-84 system, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System

lon.description: Geographic longitude (east-west axis) in WGS-84 system, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System

image.description: Uniform resource locator, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uniform_Resource_Locator and https://mathiasbynens.be/demo/url-regex

passengers.description: The number of passengers this vehicle will be able to transport

doors.description: The number of doors this car model may have - an array of min & max

luggage.description: The number of luggage this vehicle will be able to transport - an array of [big, small] luggage

classification.description: ACRISS classification of the car, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ACRISS_Car_Classification_Code

registrationPlate.description: Registration plate (e.g. if we know the actual car already)

damage.description: Any reported damages to the car (if available)

fuelLevel.description: The percentage of fuel the car has at the moment

vehicleId.description: The taxi id (in the taxi number plate on top of the vehicle)

vehicleLocation.description: Geographic latitude-longitude object in WGS-84 system, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System

lat.description: Geographic latitude (north-south axis) in WGS-84 system, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System

lon.description: Geographic longitude (east-west axis) in WGS-84 system, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System

vehicleDescription.description: An arbitrary description of the vehicle, e.g. 'Black Jaguar'

image.description: Uniform resource locator, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uniform_Resource_Locator and https://mathiasbynens.be/demo/url-regex

terms.description: MaaS booking terms and condition for its business engine

type.description: A type of ticket/product that this booking is valid for - should be unique within a given region, e.g. 'Single ticket / Lhiseutu 2'. When reusing the tickets in maas-backend, the 'type' field is checked for equality.

token.description: The validity token (such as booking ID, travel ticket etc.) that MaaS clients will display to validate the trip when starting the leg.

validityDuration.description: The rules that MaaS will interpret to schedule, re-validate or cancel the booking.

startTime.description: The starting time from which the ticket is valid

endTime.description: The finishing time the ticket is valid for

data.description: Arbitrary ticket data for the client

meta.description: Arbitrary metadata the TSP may pass along the ticket to the client (e.g. a booking code, base64 encoded binary)
